Good catch @vperumal! We can quickly do it this way to unblock. However, I think it will be a good practice to do it in the following way because we are using multithreading for all ASICs:
```
 if bfd_up_count != expected_bfd_up_count:
 check_result["failed"] = True
 else:
 # all ASICs that have reported so far
 all_ok = all(
 count == expected_bfd_up_count
 for count in check_result["bfd_up_count"].values()
 )
 check_result["failed"] = not all_ok
```

I will create a separate PR for the above optimization. Let's merge your quick fix for now. Thanks! cc. @yejianquan

